title: Christiane Amanpour confronts CNN brass about “double standards” on Israel coverage
description: CNN employees, including the renowned international news anchor Christiane Amanpour, confronted network executives over what the staffers described as myriad leadership failings in coverage of Israel’s war on Gaza, according to a leaked recording of a recent all-hands meeting obtained by The Intercept.

title: Ayatollah Emami Kashani passes away
description: TEHRAN – Ayatollah Mohammad Emami Kashani, a member of the Assembly of Experts, passed away in his home in Tehran because of heart arrest on Saturday night.

title: Scholz vows probe into 'very serious' leak of army talks on Ukraine war
description: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz on Saturday promised a full investigation after what appeared to be a recording of confidential army talks on the Ukraine war was posted on Russian social media, in a potentially huge embarrassment for Berlin.

title: Iranian, Saudi ambassadors engage in diplomatic dialogue
description: TEHRAN- The Iranian Ambassador to Riyadh, Alireza Enayati, engaged in constructive discussions with his Saudi counterpart, Abdullah bin Saud Al-Anzi.

title: Iranian Army Chief commends forces for securing land, air, sea borders during elections
description: TEHRAN - The chief commander of the Iranian Army expressed gratitude towards the coordinated efforts of the Iranian Ground, Navy, and Aerial forces, alongside defense chiefs, in ensuring the smooth conduct of Iran's March 1 elections.

title: Hezbollah’s skilled shooters humiliate the Zionist Air Force
description: After four months of accumulating tactical and strategic achievements, the Lebanese Islamic Resistance's behavior confirms the keenness of its leadership to deprive the Zionist enemy of restoring the prestige of deterrence.  Therefore, the shooting down of the “Zik-Hermes 450 drone,” which has advanced maneuvering and targeting capabilities, on February 26, is an objective response to the enemy’s threats.  The question that pops up is: Does the new escalation and the resistance’s improvement in the quality of its goals translate into a further move towards a comprehensive war?

title: Iran-Russia trade without currency transfer
description: TEHRAN - In a note, the Iran newspaper discussed a new season to increase Tehran-Moscow economic prosperity and wrote: Iran and Russia are pursuing barter trade.

title: Iran ranks 14th in ‘Global Firepower’ report on strongest armies
description: TEHRAN – In a recent report, "Global Firepower," a specialized military ranking website assessing 145 countries based on over 60 indices, has positioned Iran at the 14th spot.

title: Iran rejects role in Ukraine war
description: TEHRAN- The charge that Iran is involved in the armed confrontation between Russia and Ukraine was flatly denied by Iran’s ambassador to the UN.

title: Israeli bombings kill 7 more captives in Gaza
description: TEHRAN- Hamas has said seven more captives have been killed by Israeli airstrikes after contact was lost with the group responsible for safeguarding them.

title: Hezbollah carries out attacks in southern Israel
Political ploy
description: TEHRAN- The administration of U.S. President Joe Biden has come under growing domestic and international pressure over the past days to reconsider its unwavering support for Israel’s deadly war on the Gaza Strip.

title: Russia's Strategic Moves to Dismantle American Imperialism
description: TEHRAN- In recent years, geopolitical dynamics have underscored a significant shift in the balance of power and the strategies employed by global powers to assert their influence and manage conflicts.

title: UK ship attacked by Yemeni army sinks in Red Sea
description: A British container ship has sunk in the Red Sea almost two weeks after it came under attack by Yemen’s Armed Forces.

title: Nicaragua pursues Germany at ICJ over military support for Israel
description: Nicaragua has filed a case at the International Court of Justice (ICJ) against Germany over financial and military aid to Israel amid its war on Gaza.

title: Intl. churches urged to stop “war of genocide”
description: Ramzi Khoury, the head of the Palestinian Committee for Church Affairs, has issued a plea to international institutions and churches to raise their voices against Israel’s “massacres” in Gaza, Wafa reports.

title: UN Women calls war in Gaza "a war on women"
description: UN Women, a United Nations organization dedicated to gender equality and the empowerment of women, has called the war in Gaza "also a war on women."

title: Iranian election results: shift towards independent candidates
description: TEHRAN - As the vote counting process nears completion nationwide in Iran, following Friday's active participation at polling stations, it seems that citizens have shown a preference for individual candidates over coalitions endorsed by well-known politicians.

title: Gaza a moral compass for humanity
description: TEHRAN – Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi, currently in Algeria for the 7th meeting of the Gas Exporting Countries Forum (GECF), has warned that those remaining silent about the Gaza situation today will inevitably face severe consequences tomorrow.

title: Vahdat Hall to host performance showcasing Iranian traditions
description: TEHRAN-Tehran’s Vahdat Hall will be hosting a ritual performance on Iranian costumes and traditions on March 8.

title: Yukio Mishima’s “The Lady Aoi” on stage in Ahvaz
description: TEHRAN-The play “The Lady Aoi” written by Japanese playwright Yukio Mishima and directed by Sasan Riahipour is on stage at Aftab Theater in Ahvaz, Khuzestan Province.

title: Award-winning short animation “The Song of Flying Leaves” to compete in MCM
description: TEHRAN-The Iranian-Armenian short animation “The Song of Flying Leaves” will be screened in the 25th International Festival Music & Cinema Marseille (MCM) in France in April.

title: Iranian Film Festival returns to Malaysian screens after five-year hiatus
description: TEHRAN-The 2024 Iranian Film Festival in Malaysia, organized by Iran's cultural attaché office in Kuala Lumpur and supported by the Embassy of the Islamic Republic of Iran in Malaysia, is making its grand return to selected GSC cinemas after a prolonged absence of five years.

title: Iran's Aminzadeh bags gold at Fazza Dubai 2024 World Cup
description: TEHRAN - Ahmad Aminzadeh of Iran won a gold medal with a record-breaking lift at the Fazza World Cup on Saturday.

title: Illegal diggers arrested near Pasargadae
description: TEHRAN –  The commander of the Cultural Heritage Protection Unit in Fars province announced the arrest of four unauthorized excavators near Pasargadae in southern Iran.

title: Ardabil sets sight on upscale hotels to woo foreign visitors
description: TEHRAN – Jafar Bazri, a member of Ardabil’s Chamber of Commerce, has revealed a substantial necessity of constructing upscale accommodations offering a lavish experience to travelers with an eye toward absorbing foreign tourists.

title: Baraghan, Salehieh listed among Iran’s top tourist villages
description: TEHRAN – Baraghan and Salehieh, situated in Iran’s Alborz province, have been included in the national list of top tourist villages.

title: Three visits, countless discoveries: a Chinese tour guide’s view of Iran
description: TEHRAN – A Chinese tour guide named Jill has painted a portrait of her encounter with Persian culture and lifestyle as she is paying a visit to Iran for the third time.

title: Human traces dating back 14,000 years discovered in southern Iran
description: TEHRAN – A team of archaeologists has found human traces in recent excavations they conducted at the rock shelters of Pir-Quch in southern Iran.

title: Power plants with 17,122MW capacity under construction by industrial sector
description: TEHRAN – Iran’s major industries are currently constructing power plants with a total capacity of 17,122 megawatts (MW) across the country to meet their electricity demands, IRNA reported.

title: TEDPIX gains 31,000 points on Saturday
description: TEHRAN- TEDPIX, the main index of the Tehran Stock Exchange (TSE), rose 31,782 points to 2,086,609 on Saturday, which is the first day of the Iranian calendar week.

title: GECF Summit: Oji calls for de-politicization of energy market
description: TEHRAN - The 7th meeting of the Gas Exporting Countries Forum (GECF) Heads of State and Government commenced in Algiers, the capital of Algeria, on Saturday with Iran’s President Ebrahim Raisi and Oil Minister Javad Oji in attendance.

title: Iran-Turkey trade surpasses $500m in January
description: TEHRAN - The trade exchanges between Iran and Turkey in January reached $501 million, showing a two percent increase compared to the same month last year.

title: Thermal power plants’ generation capacity exceeds 75,000 MW
description: TEHRAN – Iran’s thermal power plants’ electricity generation capacity has exceeded 75,000 megawatts (MW), an official with the country’s Thermal Power Plants Holding Company (TPPH) announced.

title: Iran ready to provide vocational training for Omani workforce
description: TEHRAN – Iran is ready to provide technical and vocational training for 1,000 Omani workers, the head of Iran’s Technical and Vocational Training Organization said.

title: Production of iron ore concentrate rises 7% in 10 months on year
description: TEHRAN- The production of iron ore concentrate in Iran increased by seven percent in the first 10 months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 21, 2023-January 20, 2024), as compared to the same period in the past year, according to the data released by the Iranian Mines and Mining Industries Development and Renovation Organization (IMIDRO).

title: INTA eases guarantee regulations to facilitate imports of machinery
description: TEHRAN – The head of the Iranian National Tax Administration (INTA) has announced the possibility of using guarantee checks instead of bank guarantees to submit to customs for the import of machinery and production line equipment.

title: UNEA-6 approves Iran’s proposed plan for combating SDSs
description: TEHRAN – The 6th United Nations Environment Assembly (UNEA-6) has approved a resolution adopted at the international summit on dealing with sand and dust storms which was held in Tehran in September 2023.

title: Japan, UNHCR to improve education, healthcare for refugees in Iran
description: TEHRAN – In a bid to provide Afghan refugees and host communities in Iran with quality education and healthcare services, the Government of Japan and the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees have signed a partnership agreement.

title: Intl. effort on wetlands conservation to continue: official
description: TEHRAN –The implementation of projects in cooperation with international bodies to preserve and restore wetlands in the country will continue, Mojtaba Zoljoodi, an official with the Department of Environment (DOE) has said.

title: Iran’s Bakhtiar wins gold at Fazza Dubai 2024 World Cup
description: TEHRAN – Mohsen Bakhtiar of Iran claimed a gold medal in the 13th Fazza Dubai 2024 ParaPowerlifting World Cup.

title: Raisi attends gas forum in Algeria
description: TEHRAN - President Ebrahim Raisi of Iran arrived in Algiers on Saturday to take part in a meeting of the world’s leading natural gas producers and to strengthen Tehran’s cooperation with regional and international alliances.

title: Pezhman Noor has recently started collaborating with the Conde Atocha company as an artist
description: Pezhman Noor has recently started collaborating with the Conde Atocha company as an artist. Pezhman Noor, a flamenco guitarist and composer, has recently begun his collaboration with the company as an artist and guitarist of this company. Pezhman Noor has made this happen for the first time in the Middle East. During the negotiations between Pezhman Noor and Carmen Conde, their cooperation has started since 2023.

title: Jahanbakhsh may miss Turkmenistan’s match in 2026 World Cup qualifier
description: TEHRAN – Alireza Jahanbakhsh may miss the 2026 World Cup qualifying match against Turkmenistan.

title: Iran condemns Israel’s blatant attack on Gazans who were collecting food aid
Kapogianni wants to remain Iran’s women’s basketball coach: official
description: TEHRAN –  Iran basketball federation vice-president Fattaneh Malek says that Greek head coach Eleni Kapogianni has shown interest in cooperation with Iran’s women’s team.
